For typographical reasons it is convenient to present the matrix $\Omega$
discussed in section \ref{z7} in block form:
$$
\Omega =
\ar
A & B \\
C & D
\ra
$$
where the blocks are given by
$$
A =
\arrr
u_{3} &
0 &
u_{2} &
u_{1} &
u_{1} &
u_{2}
 \\
-u_{2} &
-u_{2} + u_{3} &
-u_{2} &
0 &
u_{1} - u_{2} &
u_{1} - u_{2}
 \\
-u_{1} + u_{2} &
-u_{1} &
-u_{1} + u_{3} &
-u_{1} &
-u_{1} + u_{2} &
0
 \\
0 &
-u_{1} + u_{2} &
-u_{1} &
-u_{1} + u_{3} &
-u_{1} &
-u_{1} + u_{2}
 \\
u_{1} - u_{2} &
u_{1} - u_{2} &
0 &
-u_{2} &
-u_{2} + u_{3} &
-u_{2}
 \\
u_{2} &
u_{1} &
u_{1} &
u_{2} &
0 &
u_{3}
\ra
$$ \nonumber
$$
B =
\arrr
0 &
-u_{6} &
-u_{5} &
-u_{4} &
u_{4} &
u_{5}
 \\
u_{6} &
0 &
-u_{6} &
-u_{5} &
-u_{4} &
u_{4}
 \\
u_{5} &
u_{6} &
0 &
-u_{6} &
-u_{5} &
-u_{4}
 \\
u_{4} &
u_{5} &
u_{6} &
0 &
-u_{6} &
-u_{5}
 \\
-u_{4} &
u_{4} &
u_{5} &
u_{6} &
0 &
-u_{6}
 \\
-u_{5} &
-u_{4} &
u_{4} &
u_{5} &
u_{6} &
0
\ra \nonumber
$$
$$
C=
\arrr
0 &
-u_{9} &
-u_{8} &
-u_{7} &
-u_{8} &
-u_{9}
 \\
u_{9} &
